            <p>Charleston S. C. Dec. 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1879<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd S. Morais&#58;<lb/>
                My dear Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>I would be obliged to you<lb/> for information on the following points&#58;<lb/> My attention has been called to the<lb/> fact&#44; and I have witnessed it this<lb/> month myself&#44; that at times the<lb/> new&#45;moon is visible a day&#44; or two&#44;<lb/> &#40;anyhow <hi rend="underline">one</hi> day&#41; previous to first<lb/> day of &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; as given in the &#91;Hebrew&#93;.<lb/></p>
            <p>2nd there is a tomb&#45;stone here in<lb/> our <sic>Cemetary</sic> which has an inscription<lb/> in English&#8212;there&#39;s no <sic>hebrew</sic> on it&#8212;like<lb/> this&#58; &#34;To the memory of Mrs Sarah<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Barrett &#38;c. aged upward of one<lb/> hundred years.&#34;¬ù and under this<lb/> and <sic>seperated</sic> as the &#91;Hebrew&#93; tho&#39; not dotted<lb/> are these letters&#58; S.A.G.D.E.G.  There&#39;s<lb/> no stone like it and no one here can<lb/> interpret its meaning.  I thought<lb/> that perhaps the letters are intended<lb/> to take the place of the &#91;&#63;&#93; in Spanish or another language<lb/></p> 
            <p>With kind regards &#38; thanks.<lb/>
                Yours Very Truly&#44;<lb/>
                David Levy.<lb/></p>
        </body>
